In sum, COVID-19 resembles 1957 influenza pandemic in certain epidemiological ways (despite different pathogen & different age curve), which is what makes it more alarming than other pandemics that periodically afflict us. We're still not certain, but will know more soon. 21/

Mortality in the 1957 global flu pandemic was U-shaped, with the very young and very old dying (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8877331). This is typical, but this appears NOT to be the case with COVID-19, where the young are spared (https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.03.04.20031104v1 ). 8/

A classic 1961 paper analyzing the 1957 pandemic https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/13758900 concluded that the disease likely started in central China (like COVID-19) and became known to the rest of the world in April of 1957. Pandemics have started in many continents. 6/
